You said it yourself.

00:23:58.040 --> 00:23:59.915
BJ NOVAK: I'll read the
other one I mentioned

00:23:59.915 --> 00:24:03.075
too, "Wikipedia Brown."

00:24:03.075 --> 00:24:04.200
Let's see if I can find it.

00:24:04.200 --> 00:24:04.440
There we go.

00:24:04.440 --> 00:24:04.920
TODD WOMACK: I read that one.

00:24:04.920 --> 00:24:05.470
I enjoyed that one a bit.

00:24:05.470 --> 00:24:06.303
BJ NOVAK: Thank you.

00:24:09.340 --> 00:24:12.540
This is called "Wikipedia Brown
and the Case of the Missing

00:24:12.540 --> 00:24:16.260
Bicycle." "It was
a quiet Sunday.

00:24:16.260 --> 00:24:18.220
Wikipedia Brown was
sipping lemonade

00:24:18.220 --> 00:24:20.280
with his friend, Sally,
when all of a sudden,

00:24:20.280 --> 00:24:23.510
their classmate, Joey,
ran in, out of breath.

00:24:23.510 --> 00:24:24.810
'Help,' said Joey.

00:24:24.810 --> 00:24:26.420
'Someone stole my bike.

00:24:26.420 --> 00:24:30.920
I left it outside the
library this morning.

00:24:30.920 --> 00:24:33.770
Who stole it?'

00:24:33.770 --> 00:24:36.380
'The modern day chain bicycle
was patented in Germany

00:24:36.380 --> 00:24:41.110
in 1877,' said Wikipedia Brown.

00:24:41.110 --> 00:24:43.670
'10-speed bikes became
popular in the United States

00:24:43.670 --> 00:24:45.300
in the 1970s.

00:24:45.300 --> 00:24:49.290
Carrot Top uses a bicycle as a
prop in his popular mainstream

00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:50.620
comedy act.'

00:24:50.620 --> 00:24:52.880
'Oh, Carrot Top,' said Joey.

00:24:52.880 --> 00:24:55.900
'What ever happened
to that guy?'

00:24:55.900 --> 00:25:00.050
'Carrot Top was born Scott
Thompson in Big Bear City,

00:25:00.050 --> 00:25:04.920
California, in 1965,'
said Wikipedia Brown.

00:25:04.920 --> 00:25:06.130
'Big Bear City?

00:25:06.130 --> 00:25:07.060
What an odd name.

00:25:07.060 --> 00:25:09.710
Is that a real
place?' asked Joey.

00:25:09.710 --> 00:25:11.750
'Big Bear City is
an unincorporated

00:25:11.750 --> 00:25:15.450
census-designated place in San
Bernardino County, California,

00:25:15.450 --> 00:25:16.720
with a population of--'

00:25:16.720 --> 00:25:21.110
'Wait, let's not get
distracted,' said Sally.

00:25:21.110 --> 00:25:26.560
'Every time we talk to Wikipedia
Brown, we get distracted.

00:25:26.560 --> 00:25:28.880
We spend hours and
hours with him,

00:25:28.880 --> 00:25:32.530
and always forget what we
were supposed to investigate

00:25:32.530 --> 00:25:34.860
in the first place.'

00:25:34.860 --> 00:25:36.250
'Yes, good point,' said Joey.

00:25:36.250 --> 00:25:37.710
'We have to find my bike.

00:25:37.710 --> 00:25:40.600
Sally, do you have any ideas?'

00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:45.290
'Sally is a bad detective
and a well-known slut,' said

00:25:45.290 --> 00:25:46.120
Wikipedia Brown.

00:25:48.770 --> 00:25:54.750
'Citation needed.'

00:25:54.750 --> 00:25:59.445
'Is-- is that true?' asked
Joey, his intentions unclear.

00:26:03.850 --> 00:26:06.220
'No,' said Sally,
fuming with anger.

00:26:06.220 --> 00:26:07.470
'I don't know told him that.

00:26:07.470 --> 00:26:11.890
It could've been anyone,
literally anyone.'

00:26:11.890 --> 00:26:15.160
'The government caused 9/11,'
said Wikipedia Brown suddenly

00:26:15.160 --> 00:26:17.510
for no reason.

00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:20.370
Sally pulled
Wikipedia Brown aside.

00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:23.120
'Are you sure you're
OK, Wikipedia?'

00:26:23.120 --> 00:26:25.880
'I'm not perfect,'
said Wikipedia Brown.

00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:27.500
'I never said I was.

00:26:27.500 --> 00:26:29.380
But I work fast,
and I work for free.

00:26:29.380 --> 00:26:32.100
And that's all anyone seems
to care about these days.

00:26:32.100 --> 00:26:34.170
Plus, I'm getting
better by the second,

00:26:34.170 --> 00:26:38.010
and it's all thanks to people
like you.' Sally smiled.

00:26:38.010 --> 00:26:41.000
She liked being part
of Wikipedia's process.

00:26:41.000 --> 00:26:43.145
'OK, Wikipedia,' said Sally.

00:26:43.145 --> 00:26:45.180
'But I have a question
for you, Joey.

00:26:45.180 --> 00:26:47.350
You say you left your
bike outside the library

00:26:47.350 --> 00:26:48.540
this morning.

00:26:48.540 --> 00:26:50.320
It's Sunday morning.

00:26:50.320 --> 00:26:55.550
The library's closed.' Wikipedia
Brown stood up with a start.

00:26:55.550 --> 00:26:59.540
'Barack Obama is the father of
Miley Cyrus' baby,' announced

00:26:59.540 --> 00:27:01.290
Wikipedia Brown.

00:27:01.290 --> 00:27:04.410
This story is under review."

00:27:04.410 --> 00:27:04.980
Thank you.

00:27:09.864 --> 00:27:11.030
TODD WOMACK: Very well done.

00:27:11.030 --> 00:27:11.910
We have those in the back.

00:27:11.910 --> 00:27:12.730
Don't be shy, guys.

00:27:12.730 --> 00:27:13.640
Oh, you got one.

